Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.85,0:00:04.55,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Two people's deductions and suspense\Nfill the gulf between love and hate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.55,0:00:06.48,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The mysterious revolving Chinese table!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.48,0:00:08.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran's memories come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.35,0:00:09.99,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.99,0:00:11.75,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.75,0:00:13.76,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:59.30,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}With a gift certificate that Ran won in a drawing at a shopping mall,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.76,0:02:03.47,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}we headed to Chinatown in Yokohama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.37,0:02:07.43,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There, we met people in the movie industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.01,0:02:11.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Film director Kaizo Isogami{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.68,0:02:14.60,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Assistant director Motohiro Ito{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.17,0:02:18.31,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The author of the book, Keigo Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.98,0:02:21.71,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the producer, Shiro Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.71,0:02:24.57,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Circumstances led to us having dinner with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.17,0:02:26.51,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But, suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.04,0:02:39.68,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r} died.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.89,0:02:44.77,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}No poison was found on his clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.77,0:02:48.81,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Because there was a chemical reaction on the plate and towel that he used,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.81,0:02:54.79,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}old man Mouri, who had been sitting next to him, was suspected of planting the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.62,0:02:11.13,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(500,0)}Kaizo Isogami (52)\NMovie Director
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.29,0:02:14.63,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Motohiro Ito (38)\NAssistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.75,0:02:18.34,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Keigo Kitaura (29)\NOriginal Author
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.43,0:02:21.68,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiro Kawabata (46)\NProducer
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.67,0:02:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.24,0:03:04.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I poison a guy I'd just met\Nat a restaurant I'd never been to before?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:07.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but your story sounds too good to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:11.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The minute you show up at this place,\Nyour daughter gets scouted for a movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.67,0:03:13.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.33,0:03:16.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a total coincidence that\Nwe came here the same time as...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.65,0:03:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.05,0:03:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? You look pale.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.05,0:03:31.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay! Just felt a little dizzy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.67,0:03:37.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat! I'm sure Uncle will crack the case soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:40.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:42.65,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:46.69,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran's acting weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.69,0:03:50.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We have to get her to a hospital soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:57.17,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,(Part 2)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:06.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the towel was poisoned after the soup was spilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:10.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the waiter brought the new chopsticks and the victim switched seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.42,0:04:16.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid you're still the chief suspect!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.18,0:04:17.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.85,0:04:19.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:20.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Ranâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:21.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.40,0:04:28.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found this bottle in the restroom!\NWe think it contained the poison!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.44,0:04:29.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.19,0:04:36.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You took the towel into the restroom and poisoned it there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.00,0:04:39.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.46,0:04:42.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's true, Uncle Kogoro {\i1}can't{\i0} be the bad guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.97,0:04:47.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't been to the bathroom since we got here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:50.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Like he said, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:56.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And after Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wiped off the soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.28,0:04:59.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he held onto the towel while he{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} chan{\r}ged seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:02.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think anybody could've switched towels on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.48,0:05:05.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, there must be a way...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.42,0:05:08.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Some way to switch the towels without being noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:12.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:18.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer used the lazy Susan on the table!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.25,0:05:26.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He put the towel on the edge of the lazy Susan and skillfully rotated it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.21,0:05:30.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it'd fall into Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s lap!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:32.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.14,0:05:34.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you say "How's that"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.39,0:05:38.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If something like that falls, everybody will find it strange, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.19,0:05:43.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, that's why it has to be done cleverly so nobody notices...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.04,0:05:49.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If nobody sees it, the speed with which the lazy Susan has to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.12,0:05:52.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to drop off the towel would make all the plates fall off, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.91,0:05:59.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And why would he decide to use that towel rather than his own?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.89,0:06:02.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.31,0:06:04.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:08.46,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When I tried to get the soy sauce and the chili oil,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.17,0:06:12.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the lazy Susan kept revolving, so it was really hard to reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:18.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I remember correctly, the dishes on the table, moving clockwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.54,0:06:26.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}were twice-cooked pork, pepper steak, crab omelette,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:33.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}century eggs and sweet-and-sour pork, plus the lid of the steamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.54,0:06:20.25,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}{\fad(0,250)}Twice cooked pork{Hui guo rou}{Some of these have English names, I'm not familiar with most of them but they seem to get it right for the ones I know}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:22.71,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Pepper Steak
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.46,0:06:25.13,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Crab Omelette
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:27.76,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Century Egg
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.51,0:06:30.14,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Sweet and Sour Pork
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:32.72,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Steamer Lid
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.76,0:06:35.97,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Soy Sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:38.77,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Chili Oil
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.69,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawabata
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.94,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.07,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kitaura
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.28,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.91,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Isogami
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.41,0:06:54.24,Character Card,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:36.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The soy sauce was between the sweet and sour pork and the century eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.21,0:06:39.20,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the chili oil was between the twice cooked pork and the steamer lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:45.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Starting clockwise from the victim, Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}, the seating attangement was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.81,0:06:54.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}me, Ran, Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}, Ito{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}, Isogami{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}, and the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.76,0:06:57.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The soy sauce kept returning to the old man,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.64,0:07:01.84,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the chili oil kept returning to Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.81,0:07:05.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Come to think of it, Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.48,0:07:13.09,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I'm allergic to eggs. I can't even stand to {\i1}look{\i0} at egg dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.56,0:07:17.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Can't even stand to look at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.95,0:07:25.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, work on this area with caution.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:26.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.37,0:07:28.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.91,0:07:29.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.60,0:07:32.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.44,0:07:33.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you checked the dishes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.65,0:07:39.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you checked the tabletop for poison too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.39,0:07:40.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.32,0:07:42.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:46.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Did you check that part?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.98,0:07:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, we haven't looked there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.14,0:07:53.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Kogoro just wanted to know if you had!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.68,0:07:56.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sleeping Kogoro said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.51,0:08:01.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and did you find anything funny on the poisoned towel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:04.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean apart from the poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.65,0:08:11.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, actually there was this light brown stain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.20,0:08:14.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I took a whiff of it, but it's probably just soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:21.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw when Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} spilled soup on his trousers and cleaned it off with the towel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:24.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it got that stain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.50,0:08:25.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What else?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:27.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything else on the towel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.82,0:08:30.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.21,0:08:35.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, I see... Nothing else on it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.22,0:08:39.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell Uncle Kogoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.22,0:08:41.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.00,0:08:43.27,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:48.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} didn't die from that poisoned hand towel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:50.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The towel was planted after he was killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.33,0:08:55.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And I know who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.93,0:09:01.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In that case, the evidence should still be there...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.51,0:09:03.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On the table...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.07,0:09:11.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.73,0:09:15.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer went to the restroom,\Npoisoned his own hand towel,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.47,0:09:19.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and swapped it with the victim's towel during the meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.34,0:09:23.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And somehow he did it without me, Ran or Conan noticing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.15,0:09:26.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,even though we were right next to the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.96,0:09:30.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I don't get. How'd he pull it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.92,0:09:32.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:35.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All three suspects are from the movie industry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.45,0:09:39.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer used special effects,\Nlike invisible strings...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Get real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.81,0:09:51.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, the air conditioning's turned up way too high.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.31,0:09:54.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Inspector Yokomizo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:57.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Oh, nothing. My brother told me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.65,0:10:03.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that Kogoro Mouri's deductions seem way off target at first, but he's just playing dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:08.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He turns into a different person after he lets out a strange cry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:12.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and does this weird dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:17.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I bet my brother was just making that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.98,0:10:19.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.21,0:10:25.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you mean by a weird dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:36.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we've chatted long enough.\NIt's time for you to take your seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.39,0:10:40.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right... The people who were sitting at the table with the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:45.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and Kitamura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you three.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.91,0:10:53.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I'll tell you everything about this case\Nand what happened during the fateful meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.97,0:10:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Look! It's Sleeping Kogoro's famous deduction routine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.13,0:11:03.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Yokomizo, please take the victim's seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.98,0:11:11.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the rest of us. From his right, that's me and Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.02,0:11:14.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then Ito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and then Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.86,0:11:20.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and could another officer take Ran's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.21,0:11:22.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.52,0:11:26.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter isn't feeling well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.45,0:11:27.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:31.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.70,0:11:35.81,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:41.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, please sit between the victim and Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.58,0:11:51.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we're all seated, I'd like to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.58,0:11:55.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,about the strange incident just before the victim's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.20,0:11:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Strange incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.34,0:12:02.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lazy Susan! Somebody was playing tricks on me by moving the lazy Susan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:04.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.25,0:12:08.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see the bottle of soy sauce on the lazy Susan right in front of Uncle Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.90,0:12:10.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:13.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I turned the lazy Susan to get the soy sauce.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:14.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But whenever I reached for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.74,0:12:18.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it turned again and the sauce went back to Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.08,0:12:19.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:24.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing happened with the chili oil in front of Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.99,0:12:28.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Each time the bottle came close to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:31.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it would go back right away to being in front of Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.06,0:12:35.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This means that someone was having fun, giving me a hard time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.45,0:12:41.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mr. Detective, does what this kid's saying have anything to do with the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.62,0:12:45.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.89,0:12:48.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.76,0:12:55.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uncle Kogoro told me the murderer will turn himself in! You guys don't need to do a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.01,0:12:57.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Turn himself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.07,0:13:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are, little boy. A pork bun!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.33,0:13:03.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh boy! Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.14,0:13:05.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey... why now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.29,0:13:09.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I was told that Detective Mouri wanted me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.64,0:13:13.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to bring the boy a pork bun while he discussed the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.17,0:13:16.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yum! It looks great!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.30,0:13:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs64}Don't eat that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.84,0:13:23.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:28.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about it! We're sitting at a table where a murder took place just moments ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.17,0:13:31.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There may still be poison on the table!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.00,0:13:34.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You want this kid to eat something with his hands after he's been touching the table?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.80,0:13:39.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But, the people from the crime lab didn't find any poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.32,0:13:42.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:45.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There may still be poison left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.49,0:13:49.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere we wouldn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.09,0:14:01.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.33,0:14:03.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough with the tease!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:07.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the murderer, and where'd he put the poison?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:10.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How would you turn this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.16,0:14:10.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:13.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lazy Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.78,0:14:17.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How? I'd just put my hand on it like so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:21.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if the plates are close together and sticking out over the edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.72,0:14:23.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,like the crab omelette and the century egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:30.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, i-in that case, I guess I'd have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.81,0:14:33.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd hold the edge of the lazy Susan like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:36.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The poison was on the {\i1}underside{\i0} of the lazy Susan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:46.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. There's no way to get the victim to touch a specific spot under the lazy Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.64,0:14:51.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if that spot was under a dish Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:56.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it was under a dish\Nhe didn't even want to look at?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.82,0:15:01.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there a dish like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.08,0:15:04.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes! Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was allergic to eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.26,0:15:08.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Look carefully, Inspector Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:14.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When those two dishes are in front of the victim's seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.98,0:15:16.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,where is the chili oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.81,0:15:21.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of Kitaura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.14,0:15:23.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.73,0:15:26.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The kid kept trying to get the chili oil,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:28.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the murderer kept trying to move the lazy Susan back into place!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:32.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted the victim to touch the underside of the lazy Susan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.07,0:15:35.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to move the two egg dishes aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.38,0:15:41.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That may have been true for the chili oil, but the soy sauce should've been right front of the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.41,0:15:46.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the table turn when he tried to get the soy sauce?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:50.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want the victim to touch the poison, you have to put the poison on the table first!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.63,0:15:56.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The murderer coated the underside of the lazy Susan with poison
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.38,0:15:59.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,right before the waiter brought the Peking duck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.76,0:16:05.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If he'd done it earlier, somebody else might have accidentally touched it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:12.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the murderer hadn't placed the poison when the kid tried to get the soy sauce?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.46,0:16:13.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.03,0:16:17.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing the murderer saw the waiter coming out with the Peking duck
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.85,0:16:22.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and started to put the poison in place under the egg dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.40,0:16:24.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But then Conan turned the lazy Susan. The murderer had to keep turning it back
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.63,0:16:26.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to apply the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:30.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the person who had the egg dishes in front of him
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.76,0:16:33.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when the soy sauce was in front of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.50,0:16:40.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. In other words, that's the person who poisoned Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.97,0:16:43.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.78,0:16:53.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then where'd the poisoned towel come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.68,0:16:57.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s towel from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:01.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He took it to the restroom, put cyanide on it, went back to the seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.74,0:17:07.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and pressed it against the underside of the lazy Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} collapsed, he used the confusion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.53,0:17:15.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to switch his towel with Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.63,0:17:21.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He also stained his towel with soup to make it look like Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.63,0:17:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after he had wiped the soup off his trousers, so nobody would realize it'd been switched.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:32.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you forgot one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.01,0:17:35.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was wearing blue jeans!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:43.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Kawabata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s towel, which you still have on you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.46,0:17:46.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,has both a soup stain...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.45,0:17:50.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and a faint {\i1}blue{\i0} stain from the jeans.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.25,0:17:59.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... If Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has this towel,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.48,0:18:04.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it's clear evidence that he's the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.09,0:18:08.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It isn't {\i1}solid{\i0} evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.64,0:18:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility that someone else planted it there to pin the crime on Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:20.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I think it's time you confessed, Isogami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.06,0:18:29.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You stopped Conan from eating that bun\Nafter touching the poisoned lazy Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.25,0:18:36.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you still have a conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.51,0:18:44.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A conscience?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.77,0:19:00.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If that guy had one of those, he wouldn't have let Rika die,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.13,0:19:03.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and I wouldn't have been forced to take revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.28,0:19:07.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rika? The actress who died last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.96,0:19:10.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was an accident at a film shoot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.12,0:19:13.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was no accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.78,0:19:19.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.88,0:19:23.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The last action scene was supposed to be done by a stunt woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.36,0:19:25.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but Rika took her place at the last minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.30,0:19:28.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Kawabata let her get killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.47,0:19:31.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.55,0:19:32.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.62,0:19:39.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After she died, he told me with a smirk that he'd just given her what she wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.49,0:19:45.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to her work, the movie was a big hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.13,0:19:49.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had every opportunity to stop her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.19,0:19:59.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't get it. You always complained about her... said she was an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:02.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:06.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A director's job is a sad one...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.33,0:20:12.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you see how easy it is to fall for a star when you see her through the camera lens?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.35,0:20:19.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter how poor her acting is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.61,0:20:26.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't understand that love,\Nyou'll always be an assistant director.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.04,0:20:29.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.41,0:20:32.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us the rest at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:42.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Detective, I'm sure you wiped the poison off the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:47.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But what were you going to do if I hadn't shouted at the kid, and let him die?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.28,0:20:52.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were a heartless guy like Kawabata?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.63,0:20:57.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I was going to interrogate you with stronger words.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.81,0:21:02.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Words you'd never be able to talk yourself out of...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:05.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.90,0:21:12.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I oughta complain to God for giving me a conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:20.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,As a film maker, I'd have loved to have seen a real performance from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.42,0:21:24.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I've never been the kind of guy\Nto believe in God or Buddha...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.55,0:21:26.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}God...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:31.50,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Does this world even {\i1}have{\i0} a God?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:34.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Whose voice was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.91,0:21:39.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A calm female voice... Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.48,0:21:41.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.46,0:21:43.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.91,0:21:47.43,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The sound of the rain is dying down...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.03,0:21:49.46,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...need a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.82,0:21:51.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I think I can hear what he's saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.28,0:21:54.44,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Do you need a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.20,0:21:59.30,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Do you need a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.62,0:22:02.46,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Does this world even {\i1}have{\i0} a God?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.00,0:22:04.25,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Are you Japanese?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.78,0:22:09.53,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At least, no angel ever smiled on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.53,0:22:11.48,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Beat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.48,0:22:12.88,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Not even once...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.27,0:22:14.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sharon...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.88,0:22:18.39,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I remember... It was back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.39,0:22:20.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I met him...{manga: referent is Akai -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.28,0:22:24.73,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}When I went there with Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.53,0:22:29.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,1000)}Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.61,0:24:03.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there! Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.82,0:24:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.83,0:24:07.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran is... Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0} is...!
